Add Filters to a Data Lake Object

Use filters on the data lake object (DLO) field attributes to view region-specific or brand-specific data. Adding the same DLO to multiple data spaces with different filters helps you segregate data.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To add filters to data lake objects	Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist
In Data Cloud, go to the Data Spaces tab.
Select a data space.
From the dropdown next to the Data Objects, select Set Filters.
Click Add Filter.
Select an object, column, and operator, and enter a value to filter on. To filter data on one or more values, use either the EQUALS or IN operator. Nested operators aren’t supported. You can add filters only on the non-key qualifier fields.
Click Add, and then click Save.
EXAMPLE

You have a Sales org with contacts from different regions connected to Data Cloud, and the contact DLOs are ingested with all the contacts. To segregate the contacts, you create region-specific data spaces, such as Region 1 and Region 2, and associate the contact DLOs to these data spaces with different filters. You can add two filters. You can select Region for the column, EQUALS for the operator, and enter region 1 as the value. For the other filter, enter region 2 for the value.
